About
This repository contains my notes and practice code from CSE114: Introduction to Java.
The course introduced the fundamentals of programming with Java, starting from basic syntax and programming logic to object-oriented programming and introductory data structures. I created this repository to organize what I learned throughout the semester and to use it as a reference for future courses and personal projects.
Topics Covered
Java Basics
* Variables
* Primitive Data Types
* Operators
* User Input & Output
* Type Casting
Control Flow
* if / else
* switch
* for loops
* while loops
* do-while loops
Methods
* Defining methods
* Parameters
* Return values
* Method overloading
* Variable scope
Object-Oriented Programming
* Classes and Objects
* Constructors
* Instance Variables
* Static Variables
* Encapsulation
* Access Modifiers
* Getter & Setter
* Method Overloading
* Method Overriding
Arrays
* One-dimensional arrays
* Two-dimensional arrays
* Searching
Data Structures
* Array
* Linked List
* ArrayList
* Stack
* Queue
What I Learned
After completing this course, I can:
* Write programs using Java.
* Design classes using object-oriented programming.
* Choose appropriate data structures for simple problems.
* Break problems into smaller methods.
* Read, debug, and improve Java code.


Future Plans
I plan to continue updating this repository as I learn more advanced Java topics such as Generics, Collections, Exception Handling, File I/O, and Multithreading.
